            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I like the proposal and think it would be a great addition to the stdlib. \n\nSmall comment: although I do really like the convenience functions `vim.net.get` and `vim.net.post`, it might not immediately be clear to users with less knowledge of HTTP and networking what `vim.net.delete` and `vim.net.options` do. Although less clean, maybe just having `vim.net.req('delete', opts, on_resp)` etc. would be more readable. ",
