        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "If any improvements are to be made to `vim.net`, I think it's worth mentioning `vim._transport` and `vim._framer` in [this PR](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39000). They seem helpful for implementing streaming, rather than having to return only after all results have been returned.\n\nRegarding the HTTP client, I personally feel that functions like `vim.net.get` or `vim.net.post` will eventually share a more powerful underlying function, serving merely as simple wrappers for that primary request function. Therefore, I don't think separate interfaces like `vim.net.get` are particularly meaningful; they just add to our burden of API maintenance. We only need to ensure that a single universal interface is simple enough to use for `get` or `post` requests.",
            "created_at": "2026-04-15T07:38:00Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38946#issuecomment-4250136844",
            "id": 4250136844,
