        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@ofseed about:\n\n> If any improvements are to be made to vim.net, I think it's worth mentioning vim._transport and vim._framer in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39000. They seem helpful for implementing streaming, rather than having to return only after all results have been returned.\n\nthat would be a good improvement for sure. \n\n\n> Regarding the HTTP client, I personally feel that functions like vim.net.get or vim.net.post will eventually share a more powerful underlying function, serving merely as simple wrappers for that primary request function. Therefore, I don't think separate interfaces like vim.net.get are particularly meaningful; they just add to our burden of API maintenance\n\nEven if they are just convenience methods? \n\n\n@justinmk about: \n\n> An overload isn't breaking; method as first arg is a nice readability improvement imo.\n\nWhen you say \"overload\" do you mean supporting both signatures or can we just stick with the new one?\n",
